{"title_page": "Iv\u00e1n Jaime", "text_new": "{{short description|Spanish footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Iv\u00e1n Jaime\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| full_name = Iv\u00e1n Jaime Pajuelo\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|2000|9|26|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[M\u00e1laga]], Spain\n| height = 1.80m<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.malagacf.com/jugador/ivan-jaime|title=Iv\u00e1n Jaime|publisher=M\u00e1laga CF|language=es|accessdate=6 January 2019}}</ref>\n| position = [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[M\u00e1laga CF|M\u00e1laga]]\n| clubnumber = 33\n| youthyears1 = 2005\u20132009 | youthclubs1 = Roma Luz\n| youthyears2 = 2009\u20132011 | youthclubs2 = Conejito\n| youthyears3 = 2011\u20132017 | youthclubs3 = [[M\u00e1laga CF|M\u00e1laga]]\n| years1 = 2017\u2013 | clubs1 = [[Atl\u00e9tico Malague\u00f1o|M\u00e1laga B]] | caps1 = 36 | goals1 = 3\n| years2 = 2018\u2013 | clubs2 = [[M\u00e1laga CF|M\u00e1laga]] | caps2 = 0 | goals2 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2018\u20132019 | nationalteam1 = [[Spain national under-19 football team|Spain U19]] | nationalcaps1 = 4 | nationalgoals1 = 1\n| club-update = 19 May 2019\n| nationalteam-update = 16 January 2019\n}}\n\n'''Iv\u00e1n Jaime Pajuelo''' (born 26 September 2000) is a Spanish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[M\u00e1laga CF]] as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[M\u00e1laga]], [[Andalusia]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://eldesmarque.com/malaga/malaga-cf/malaga-noticias/164401-ivan-jaime-el-cuarto-canterano-de-muniz |title= Iv\u00e1n Jaime, el cuarto canterano de Mu\u00f1iz |trans-title=Iv\u00e1n Jaime, the fourth youth player of Mu\u00f1iz |publisher=El Desmarque |language=es |date=11 September 2018 |access-date=11 September 2018}}</ref> Jaime joined [[M\u00e1laga CF]]'s youth setup in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eldesmarque.com/malaga/malaga-cf/malaga-noticias/172352-ivan-jaime-y-hugo-queremos-salvar-al-filial|title=Iv\u00e1n Jaime y Hugo: \"Nuestro objetivo es salvar al filial\"|trans-title=Iv\u00e1n Jaime and Hugo: \"Our goal is to save the reserves\"|publisher=El Desmarque|language=es|date=29 November 2018|accessdate=6 January 2019}}</ref> He made his senior debut with [[Atl\u00e9tico Malague\u00f1o|the reserves]] on 26 November 2017, coming on as a first-half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a 1\u20130 [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]] away win against Villacarrillo CF.\n\nOn 11 September 2018, fifteen days shy of his 18th birthday, Jaime made his first-team debut by replacing fellow debutant [[Abdel Abqar]] in a 1\u20132 home loss against [[UD Almer\u00eda]] for [[2018\u201319 Copa del Rey|the season]]'s [[Copa del Rey]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/futbol/copa-rey/cronica/2018/09/11/5b980ec5e5fdea0a1c8b4593.html|title=El Almer\u00eda remonta al M\u00e1laga y pasa a la siguiente ronda|trans-title=Almer\u00eda complete comeback over M\u00e1laga and go to the following round|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=11 September 2018|access-date=11 September 2018}}</ref> He scored his first senior goal on 25 November, netting the opener through a [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty kick]] in a 2\u20131 home defeat of [[Atl\u00e9tico Sanluque\u00f1o CF]] for the [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B]] championship.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|21670}}\n*{{LaPreferente|150099<!-- /ivan -->}}\n*{{Soccerway|ivan-jaime-pajuelo/464314}}\n\n{{M\u00e1laga CF squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jaime, Ivan}}\n[[Category:2000 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from M\u00e1laga]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Andalusian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:Tercera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Atl\u00e9tico Malague\u00f1o players]]\n[[Category:M\u00e1laga CF players]]\n[[Category:Spain youth international footballers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Spanish footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Iv\u00e1n Jaime\n| image =\n| image_size =\n| caption =\n| fullname = Iv\u00e1n Jaime Pajuelo\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|2000|9|26|df=y}} \n| birth_place = [[M\u00e1laga]], Spain\n| height = 1.80m<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.malagacf.com/jugador/ivan-jaime|title=Iv\u00e1n Jaime|publisher=M\u00e1laga CF|language=es|accessdate=6 January 2019}}</ref>\n| position = [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[M\u00e1laga CF|M\u00e1laga]]\n| clubnumber = 33\n| youthyears1 = 2005\u20132009 | youthclubs1 = Roma Luz\n| youthyears2 = 2009\u20132011 | youthclubs2 = Conejito\n| youthyears3 = 2011\u20132017 | youthclubs3 = [[M\u00e1laga CF|M\u00e1laga]]\n| years1 = 2017\u2013 | clubs1 = [[Atl\u00e9tico Malague\u00f1o|M\u00e1laga B]] | caps1 = 36 | goals1 = 3\n| years2 = 2018\u2013 | clubs2 = [[M\u00e1laga CF|M\u00e1laga]] | caps2 = 0 | goals2 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2018\u20132019 | nationalteam1 = [[Spain national under-19 football team|Spain U19]] | nationalcaps1 = 4 | nationalgoals1 = 1 \n| club-update = 19 May 2019\n| nationalteam-update = 16 January 2019\n}}\n'''Iv\u00e1n Jaime Pajuelo''' (born 26 September 2000) is a Spanish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[M\u00e1laga CF]] as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[M\u00e1laga]], [[Andalusia]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://eldesmarque.com/malaga/malaga-cf/malaga-noticias/164401-ivan-jaime-el-cuarto-canterano-de-muniz |title= Iv\u00e1n Jaime, el cuarto canterano de Mu\u00f1iz |trans-title=Iv\u00e1n Jaime, the fourth youth player of Mu\u00f1iz |publisher=El Desmarque |language=es |date=11 September 2018 |access-date=11 September 2018}}</ref> Jaime joined [[M\u00e1laga CF]]'s youth setup in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eldesmarque.com/malaga/malaga-cf/malaga-noticias/172352-ivan-jaime-y-hugo-queremos-salvar-al-filial|title=Iv\u00e1n Jaime y Hugo: \"Nuestro objetivo es salvar al filial\"|trans-title=Iv\u00e1n Jaime and Hugo: \"Our goal is to save the reserves\"|publisher=El Desmarque|language=es|date=29 November 2018|accessdate=6 January 2019}}</ref> He made his senior debut with [[Atl\u00e9tico Malague\u00f1o|the reserves]] on 26 November 2017, coming on as a first-half [[Substitute (association football) |substitute]] in a 1\u20130 [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]] away win against Villacarrillo CF.\n\nOn 11 September 2018, fifteen days shy of his 18th birthday, Jaime made his first-team debut by replacing fellow debutant [[Abdel Abqar]] in a 1\u20132 home loss against [[UD Almer\u00eda]] for [[2018\u201319 Copa del Rey|the season]]'s [[Copa del Rey]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/futbol/copa-rey/cronica/2018/09/11/5b980ec5e5fdea0a1c8b4593.html|title=El Almer\u00eda remonta al M\u00e1laga y pasa a la siguiente ronda|trans-title=Almer\u00eda complete comeback over M\u00e1laga and go to the following round|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=11 September 2018|access-date=11 September 2018}}</ref> He scored his first senior goal on 25 November, netting the opener through a [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty kick]] in a 2\u20131 home defeat of [[Atl\u00e9tico Sanluque\u00f1o CF]] for the [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B]] championship.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|21670|Iv\u00e1n Jaime}}\n*{{LaPreferente|150099/ivan|Iv\u00e1n Jaime}}\n*{{Soccerway|ivan-jaime-pajuelo/464314|Iv\u00e1n Jaime}}\n\n{{M\u00e1laga CF squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jaime, Ivan}}\n[[Category:2000 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from M\u00e1laga]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Andalusian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:Tercera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Atl\u00e9tico Malague\u00f1o players]]\n[[Category:M\u00e1laga CF players]]\n[[Category:Spain youth international footballers]]\n", "name_user": "Zyxw", "label": "safe", "comment": "update links, misc formatting", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iv%C3%A1n_Jaime"}
{"title_page": "Pattern Recognition (journal)", "text_new": "{{Infobox journal\n| title = Pattern Recognition\n| cover = \n| editor = [[Edwin Hancock]]\n| discipline =[[Artificial intelligence]],  [[computer science]], [[pattern recognition]]\n| former names = \n| abbreviation = Pattern Recognit.\n| publisher = [[Elsevier Science]]\n| country =\n| frequency = Monthly\n| history = 1968\u2013present\n| openaccess = \n| license = \n| impact = 5.898\n| impact-year = 2018\n| website = https://www.journals.elsevier.com/pattern-recognition\n| link1 = \n| link1-name = \n| link2 = \n| link2-name = \n| JSTOR = \n| OCLC = \n| LCCN = 78004311\n| CODEN = PTNRA8\n| ISSN = 0031-3203\n| eISSN = 1873-5142\n}}\n'''''Pattern Recognition''''' is a single blind   peer reviewed  academic journal published by [[Elsevier Science]]. It was first published in 1968 by [[Pergamon Press]]. The founding editor-in-chief was [[Robert Ledley]], who was succeeded from 2009  until 2016  by Ching Suen of [[Concordia University]]. Since  2016 the current editor-in-chief is [[Edwin Hancock]] of the [[University of York]]. The journal publishes papers in the general area of [[pattern recognition]], including applications in the areas of [[image processing]], [[computer vision]], [[handwriting recognition]], [[biometrics]] and [[biomedical]] signal processing. The journal awards the Pattern Recognition Society Medal to the best paper published in the  journal each year.<ref>{{cite journal |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |title=Biennial Pattern Recognition Journal Awards 2013 and 2014 |journal=Pattern Recognition |volume=61 |issue= |pages=702 |doi=10.1016/j.patcog.2016.09.002 |year= 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |title=Biennial Pattern Recognition Journal Awards 2011 and 2012 |journal=Pattern Recognition |volume=47 |issue=12 |pages=3737 |doi=10.1016/j.patcog.2014.07.018 |year= 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |title=Biennial Pattern Recognition Journal Awards 2009 and 2010 |journal=Pattern Recognition |volume=46 |issue= 2|pages=463 |doi= 10.1016/j.patcog.2012.09.004|year= 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |title=Biennial Pattern Recognition Journal Awards 2007 and 2008 |journal=Pattern Recognition |volume=43 |issue= 12|pages=3923\u20133924 |doi=10.1016/j.patcog.2010.08.001 |year= 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |title=Biennial Pattern Recognition Journal Awards 2005 and 2006 |journal=Pattern Recognition |volume=41 |issue=12 |pages=3519\u20133520 |doi=10.1016/j.patcog.2008.08.005 |year= 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |title=Thirtieth Annual Pattern Recognition Society Award 2003 |journal=Pattern Recognition |volume=38 |issue=1 |pages=163 |doi=10.1016/j.patcog.2004.08.001 |year= 2005}}</ref><ref>\n{{cite journal |title=Twenty-ninth annual pattern recognition society award (2002)|journal= Pattern Recognition|volume= 37|issue=4| page=vii |doi= 10.1016/j.patcog.2003.10.001|year= 2004}}</ref><ref>\n{{cite journal |title=Twenty-seventh Annual Pattern Recognition Society Award |journal= Pattern Recognition|year= 2002|volume =35|issue=8|pages=I|doi=10.1016/S0031-3203(02)00055-9}}</ref><ref>\n{{ cite journal| title=Seventeenth Annual Pattern Recognition Award|doi=10.1016/0031-3203(91)90148-X |journal=Pattern Recognition|volume=24 |issue=12| pages=1225|year=1991}}</ref><ref>\n{{cite journal |title= Twelfth Annual Pattern Recognition Society Award|journal=Pattern Recognition|volume=20|issue=2|pages=265|doi=10.1016/0031-3203(87)90060-4|year=1987}}</ref><ref>\n{{cite journal |title=Eleventh Annual Pattern Recognition Society Award|journal= Pattern Recognition|volume=19|issue=4|pages=341|doi=10.1016/0031-3203(86)90060-9|year= 1986}}</ref><ref>\n{{cite journal |title=Tenth Annual Pattern Recognition Society Award| journal=Pattern Recognition|volume=18|issue=5|pages=379|doi=10.1016/0031-3203(85)90029-9| year=1985}}</ref><ref>\n{{cite journal |title=Ninth Annual Pattern Recognition Society Award|journal=Pattern Recognition|volume=17|issue=4|pages=475|doi=10.1016/0031-3203(84)90076-1|year=1984}}</ref><ref>\n{{cite journal |title=Sixth Annual Pattern Recognition Society Award|journal=Pattern Recognition|volume=13|issue=2|pages=189|doi=10.1016/0031-3203(81)90016-9|year=1981}}</ref>\nIn 2015, the journal had an impact factor of 5.898<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2016 |chapter=Pattern Recognition |title=2015 Journal Citation Reports |publisher=[[Clarivate]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]] |title-link=Journal Citation Reports }}</ref> and  it currently has a [[Scopus]] CiteScore of 7.35.<ref>{{cite journal|  journal =Pattern Recognition | title=Journal Metrics| url = https://www.journals.elsevier.com/pattern-recognition/ | accessdate=2019-06-26}}</ref> Google Scholar currently lists the journal  as ranked 6th  in the top 20  publications in Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition.<ref>{{cite journal | journal= Google Scholar | url= https://scholar.google.com/citations?view_op=top_venues&hl=en&vq=eng_computervisionpatternrecognition | title=Top publications - Computer Vision & Pattern Recognition  |accessdate=2019-06-26}}</ref>\n\n==Abstracting and indexing==\nThe journal is abstracted and indexed by the following services:\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* ''[[ACM Guide to Computing Literature]]''\n* [[BIOSIS]]\n* [[Cambridge Scientific Abstracts]]\n* Current Literature on Ageing\n* [[Current Contents]]/CompuMaths\n* [[Current Contents]]/Engineering, Computing & Technology\n* [[Current Contents]]/Social & Behavioral Sciences\n* Information Science Abstracts\n* [[Mathematical Reviews]]\n* [[Engineering Index]]\n* [[GEOBASE]]\n* [[INSPEC]]\n* Ocular R\n* PAIS Bulletin\n* PASCAL/CNRS\n* Research Alert\n* [[SCISEARCH]]\n* SSSA/CISA/ECA/ISMEC\n* [[Science Citation Index]]\n* [[Zentralblatt MATH]]\n* [[Scopus]]\n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* 