 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=3-D Nights: This short film aims to combat rising drug menace in India\n |url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/this-short-film-aims-to-combat-rising-drug-menace-in-india-119010100563_1.html |website=business standard |language=en |date=1 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=3-D Nights: This short film aims to combat rising drug menace in India\n |url=https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/entertainment/306907-short-film-3-d-nights-aims-to-tackle-rising-drug-addiction-in-india|website=devdiscourse |language=en |date=1 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n\n==Plot==\nThe [[Film]] Aim to focus on how the [[Drug]] business is become [[lucrative]] [[World|worldwide]] for drug dealers and other site, how this drug [[business]] is devastating our young [[generation]]. In this film the character of Manish Uppal is totally a [[fantasy]] an the character is only visible and exist to those people who are hell drug addicted. meanwhile in the story drug [[addicted]] people force to stay in a [[strange]] panic of fantasy character & they all found dead in a strange ways.<ref>{{cite web |title=This short film aims to combat rising drug menace in India\n |url=http://www.ianslive.in/index.php?param=news/This_short_film_aims_to_combat_rising_drug_menace_in_India-608095/ENTERTAINMENT/15 |website=ianslive |language=en |date=1 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=This short film aims to combat rising drug menace in India\n |url=https://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=561392 |website=daijiworld |language=en |date=1 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=This short film aims to combat rising drug menace in India\n |url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/this-short-film-aims-to-combat-rising-drug-menace-in-india/1450036 |website=doutlook |language=en |date=1 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=This short film aims to combat rising drug menace in India\n |url=https://www.npnews24.com/2019/01/01/this-short-film-aims-to-combat-rising-drug-menace-in-india/ |website=Npnews24 |language=en |date=1 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=3-D Nights: This short film aims to combat rising drug menace in India\n |url=http://www.thesouthasiantimes.info/news-This_short_film_aims_to_combat_rising_drug_menace_in_India-228110-Entertainment-36.html |website=thesouthasintimes|language=en |date=1 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=3-D Nights: This short film aims to combat rising drug menace in India\n |url=https://www.newkerala.com/news/read/84591/this-short-film-aims-to-combat-rising-drug-menace-in-india.html |website=newkerala |language=en |date=1 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n\n==Cast==\n* Manish Uppal as illusion\n*Deepak Nagila as dancer\n* Smriti Negi as Couple\n* Digvijay Singh as Couple\n* Sushma Prasad as Mother\n* Bhusan Chabra as Father\n\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{imdb title|9688434}}\n\n[[Category:2019 short films]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:2020 films]]\n", "text_old": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=3D Night (Film)|timestamp=20200326153735|year=2020|month=March|day=26|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=3D Night (Film)|date=26 March 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{short description|2020 film}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = 3D Night\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = Aron Mitr\n| producer       = Lucky Bisht<br>Dimple Pandey\n| writer         = Aron Mitr\n| starring       = Manish Uppal<br>Smriti Negi<br>Deepak Nagila<br>Sushma Prasad\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Shatrujit Mishra\n| editing        = Charitra raj\n| studio         = Lucky Commando Films\n| distributor    = Lucky Commando Films\n| rele